Class GameProcessor

java.lang.Object
game.GameProcessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class GameProcessor extends Object implements Serializable
The GameProcessor class is responsible for playing out the game logic.

  • Method Details

    • playLevel

      private void playLevel() throws Exception
      This method is the main game loop for playing a level that detects game commands and carries them out. The loop is active while 3 conditions are met: The player has not reached the end of the game board, the player is alive, the game is active. If an event is encountered, the method starts the event.
      Throws:
      Exception - If an error occurs while carrying out the game level logic

    • startGame

      public void startGame() throws Exception
      This method starts the game logic. The main responsibilities of the method are to set the player type and carry the level progression. If the game is custom, only one level will be played. A classic game will play up to 5 levels.
      Throws:
      Exception - If an error occurs while carrying out the game level logic

    • generateNextLevel

      private void generateNextLevel()
      Increases the level parameters. Creates a new game board and sets new player location.

    • seePlayerStats

      private void seePlayerStats()
      Shows current player stats on the system's default output stream.

    • help

      private void help()
      Shows all supported game commands on the system's default output stream.

    • jump

      private Event jump()
      Moves the player to the exit of the current game board. The command is only accessible in administrative mode.
      Returns:
      Event, appropriate for the player position on the game board

    • setHandler

      public void setHandler(InputHandler handler)
